    <title>Paper GFS - Storage, GFS and Consistency</title>
    <link href="/work/2022/09/12/dist-gfs/"/>
    <url>/work/2022/09/12/dist-gfs/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="介绍"><a href="#介绍" class="headerlink" title="介绍"></a>介绍</h3><p>We’ll talk about storage, GFS and consistency.</p><p>2003年，谷歌发布了<a href="https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.824/papers/gfs.pdf">The Google File System</a>论文。</p><p>这篇论文是谷歌大数据三驾马车中介绍最详细的一篇，其他两篇MapReduce(2004)以及BigTable(2006)介绍得并没有像GFS这样翔实。雅虎公司后续根据这三篇论文牵头做出了Hadoop开源框架，用于分布式计算和存储，主要包括两大核心组件，Hadoop DFS和Hadoop MapReduce.</p><p>由GFS也发展出不少分布式文件系统，如GlusterFS, CephFS和JuiceFS等，如下图所示：<img src="https://spongecaptain.cool/images/img_paper/image-20200723104934578.png" alt="GFS及后续分支"></p><p>GFS论文的总结可以看这篇<a href="https://spongecaptain.cool/post/paper/googlefilesystem/">博客</a>，以及针对这篇博客的<a href="https://tanxinyu.work/gfs-thesis/">提问</a>。</p><h3 id="参考文献"><a href="#参考文献" class="headerlink" title="参考文献"></a>参考文献</h3><p><a href="https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.824/notes/l-gfs.txt">6.824 讲义</a><br><a href="https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.824/papers/gfs-faq.txt">6.824 FAQ</a></p><h3 id="讲义"><a href="#讲义" class="headerlink" title="讲义"></a>讲义</h3><hr><p><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/001.jpeg" alt="001"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/002.jpeg" alt="002"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/003.jpeg" alt="003"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/004.jpeg" alt="004"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/005.jpeg" alt="005"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/006.jpeg" alt="006"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/007.jpeg" alt="007"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/008.jpeg" alt="008"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/009.jpeg" alt="009"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/010.jpeg" alt="010"></p><p><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/011.jpeg" alt="011"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/012.jpeg" alt="012"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/013.jpeg" alt="013"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/014.jpeg" alt="014"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/015.jpeg" alt="015"><br><img src="/work/img/dist-gfs/016.jpeg" alt="016"></p><hr>]]></content>
    
    
    
